{
  "A wheel rotates at 600 revolutions per minute. What is its angular velocity in rad/s?": "",
  "600 rad/s": "",
  "100 rad/s": "",
  "20π rad/s": "",
  "10π rad/s": "",
  "ω = 600 rev/min × (2π rad/rev) × (1 min/60 s) = 600(2π)/60 = 20π rad/s ≈ 62.8 rad/s.": "",
  "A disk starts from rest and reaches an angular velocity of 10 rad/s in 5 seconds with constant angular acceleration. What is the angular acceleration?": "",
  "50 rad/s²": "",
  "5 rad/s²": "",
  "0.5 rad/s²": "",
  "2 rad/s²": "",
  "α = Δω/Δt = (10 - 0)/5 = 2 rad/s².": "",
  "A point on the rim of a wheel of radius 0.5 m rotates at ω = 4 rad/s. What is its tangential speed?": "",
  "2 m/s": "",
  "4 m/s": "",
  "8 m/s": "",
  "0.125 m/s": "",
  "v = rω = 0.5(4) = 2 m/s.": "",
  "A wheel undergoes constant angular acceleration of 3 rad/s² from rest. How many radians does it rotate in 4 seconds?": "",
  "12 rad": "",
  "48 rad": "",
  "6 rad": "",
  "24 rad": "",
  "θ = ω₀t + ½αt² = 0 + ½(3)(16) = 24 rad.": "",
  "A flywheel spinning at 30 rad/s decelerates uniformly at 6 rad/s². How many revolutions does it make before stopping?": "",
  "Approximately 2.5 rev": "",
  "Approximately 5.97 rev": "",
  "Approximately 11.9 rev": "",
  "Approximately 75 rev": "",
  "ω² = ω₀² + 2αθ: 0 = 900 - 12θ, θ = 75 rad. Revolutions = 75/(2π) ≈ 11.9 rev.": "",
  "What is the centripetal acceleration of a point 0.2 m from the center of a disk rotating at 10 rad/s?": "",
  "2 m/s²": "",
  "100 m/s²": "",
  "20 m/s²": "",
  "50 m/s²": "",
  "a_c = rω² = 0.2(100) = 20 m/s².": "",
  "A merry-go-round has angular velocity ω(t) = 2t - 0.5t² rad/s. What is the angular acceleration at t = 2 s?": "",
  "0 rad/s²": "",
  "1 rad/s²": "",
  "α(t) = dω/dt = 2 - t. At t = 2 s: α = 2 - 2 = 0 rad/s².": "",
  "A bicycle wheel of radius 0.35 m has a tangential acceleration of 1.4 m/s² at its rim. What is the angular acceleration?": "",
  "0.49 rad/s²": "",
  "4 rad/s²": "",
  "0.25 rad/s²": "",
  "a_t = rα, so α = a_t/r = 1.4/0.35 = 4 rad/s².": "",
  "Two gears mesh together. Gear A has 20 teeth and Gear B has 40 teeth. If Gear A rotates at 100 rpm, what is Gear B's angular velocity?": "",
  "200 rpm": "",
  "25 rpm": "",
  "100 rpm": "",
  "50 rpm": "",
  "For meshing gears: N_A × ω_A = N_B × ω_B. 20(100) = 40(ω_B), ω_B = 50 rpm.": "",
  "A wheel of radius 0.3 m rolls without slipping at 5 m/s. What is its angular velocity?": "",
  "16.67 rad/s": "",
  "0.06 rad/s": "",
  "50 rad/s": "",
  "1.5 rad/s": "",
  "For rolling without slipping: v = rω, so ω = v/r = 5/0.3 = 16.67 rad/s.": "",
  "What is angular velocity?": "",
  "The linear speed of a rotating object": "",
  "The rate of change of angular position: ω = dθ/dt, measured in rad/s": "",
  "The force causing rotation": "",
  "The distance traveled per revolution": "",
  "Angular velocity ω = dθ/dt is the rate of change of angular position with time, measured in radians per second.": "",
  "What is angular acceleration?": "",
  "The centripetal acceleration of a rotating point": "",
  "The rate of change of angular velocity: α = dω/dt, measured in rad/s²": "",
  "The tangential speed divided by the radius": "",
  "The torque divided by the moment of inertia": "",
  "Angular acceleration α = dω/dt = d²θ/dt² is the rate at which angular velocity changes, measured in rad/s².": "",
  "What does 'tangential acceleration' mean for a point on a rotating body?": "",
  "The acceleration due to friction": "",
  "The component of acceleration directed toward the center of rotation": "",
  "The total acceleration of the point": "",
  "The component of acceleration tangent to the circular path, equal to rα": "",
  "Tangential acceleration a_t = rα is the component along the direction of motion, changing the speed of the point. It is zero when ω is constant.": "",
  "What does 'rolling without slipping' mean?": "",
  "Angular velocity equals linear velocity": "",
  "The contact point has zero velocity relative to the surface, giving the constraint v = rω": "",
  "The object rolls with no friction at all": "",
  "The object slides and rolls simultaneously": "",
  "Rolling without slipping means the contact point is instantaneously at rest relative to the surface. This gives the constraint v_cm = rω, linking translation and rotation.": "",
  "What is the relationship between linear and angular quantities in rotational motion?": "",
  "v = rω, a_t = rα, and a_c = rω²": "",
  "Linear and angular quantities are independent": "",
  "v = ω/r, a = α/r": "",
  "v = r²ω, a = r²α": "",
  "The key relationships are: tangential velocity v = rω, tangential acceleration a_t = rα, and centripetal acceleration a_c = v²/r = rω².": "",
  "What is a radian?": "",
  "The angle that corresponds to one revolution": "",
  "A unit of angular velocity": "",
  "The angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc equal in length to the radius": "",
  "One-360th of a full circle": "",
  "A radian is the angle subtended when the arc length equals the radius: θ = s/r. One full circle = 2π radians ≈ 6.28 rad.": "",
  "What is the period of rotation?": "",
  "The total angle rotated": "",
  "The time for one complete revolution: T = 2π/ω": "",
  "The number of revolutions per second": "",
  "The angular displacement per unit time": "",
  "The period T is the time for one full revolution. T = 2π/ω, where ω is the angular velocity. Frequency f = 1/T = ω/(2π).": "",
  "What is the difference between angular velocity and angular speed?": "",
  "Angular velocity is measured in rpm while angular speed is in rad/s": "",
  "They are identical quantities": "",
  "Angular velocity is a vector quantity (with direction along the axis of rotation) while angular speed is its scalar magnitude": "",
  "Angular speed includes direction but angular velocity does not": "",
  "Angular velocity ω is a vector along the rotation axis (direction by right-hand rule). Angular speed |ω| is the scalar magnitude, just how fast the rotation occurs.": "",
  "What are the rotational kinematic equations?": "",
  "Equations relating angular position, angular velocity, angular acceleration, and time for constant angular acceleration": "",
  "Equations relating torque and angular momentum": "",
  "Equations for variable angular acceleration": "",
  "Equations that only apply to objects rolling without slipping": "",
  "The rotational kinematic equations (ω = ω₀ + αt, θ = ω₀t + ½αt², ω² = ω₀² + 2αθ) are analogous to the linear kinematic equations for constant angular acceleration.": "",
  "What does 'centripetal acceleration' mean in rotational motion?": "",
  "Acceleration that causes an object to spiral outward": "",
  "Acceleration tangent to the circular path": "",
  "Acceleration directed toward the center of the circular path: a_c = v²/r = rω²": "",
  "The rate at which angular velocity changes": "",
  "Centripetal (center-seeking) acceleration points radially inward and is responsible for changing the direction of velocity: a_c = v²/r = rω².": "",
  "A car tire (radius 0.3 m) accelerates from rest to 80 km/h in 10 seconds. What is the angular acceleration of the tire, and how many revolutions does it make during this acceleration?": "",
  "α ≈ 14.8 rad/s², approximately 30 revolutions": "",
  "α ≈ 7.41 rad/s², approximately 118 revolutions": "",
  "α ≈ 7.41 rad/s², approximately 59 revolutions": "",
  "α ≈ 2.22 rad/s², approximately 18 revolutions": "",
  "80 km/h = 22.2 m/s. ω_f = v/r = 22.2/0.3 = 74.1 rad/s. α = 74.1/10 = 7.41 rad/s². θ = ½αt² = ½(7.41)(100) = 370.5 rad. Revolutions = 370.5/(2π) ≈ 59.": "",
  "A centrifuge spins biological samples at 12,000 rpm. If the samples are 0.1 m from the axis, what is the centripetal acceleration in terms of g? (g = 9.8 m/s²)": "",
